captions.translation: [JIUTAI] And so, it was in the early days of our history,
captions.transcription: [JIUTAI] Mata waga chÅ no sono hajime.

captions.translation: the Twelfth of the Imperial Line, the Emperor KeikÅ,
captions.transcription: NinnÅ jÅ«nidai KeikÅ tennÅ,

captions.translation: had a son known by the name
captions.transcription: miko no mikoto no on-na wo ba

captions.translation: Yamato-dake.
captions.transcription: Yamato-dake to mÅshishiga.

captions.translation: The wild barbarians! He received the order to subdue them.
captions.transcription: Kiui wo taiji no choku wo uke.

captions.translation: The barrier check points far behind as yet further to the East.
captions.transcription: Seki no higashi mo harukanaru.

captions.translation: The road of his journey to the Eastern provinces took him.
captions.transcription: Azuma no tabi no michi sugara

captions.translation: Even at Ise and Owari the waves on the sea rise and return!
captions.transcription: Ise ya Owari no umizura ni tatsu nami made mo

captions.translation: With envy he wondered always,
captions.transcription: kaeru koto yo to urayami

captions.translation: when he too might find himself, with foam-drenched sleeves
captions.transcription: itsu ka warera mo kaeru nami no

captions.translation: returning home, even as he continued on his way.
captions.transcription: koromode ni arama shi to omoi tsuzukete yuku hodo ni.

captions.translation: [SHITE] In the battles in one place and in the next
captions.transcription: [SHITE] Koko ya kashiko no tatakai ni

captions.translation: [JIUTAI] men and horses: their bodies crushed in their caverns,
captions.transcription: [JIUTAI] Jinba gankutsu ni mi wo kudaki,

captions.translation: their blood on the battlefields a river,
captions.transcription: Chi wa takuroku no kawa to natte,

captions.translation: their shields swept away on crimson waves again and again.
captions.transcription: kÅha tate nagashi sudo ni oyoberu Ebisu mo.

captions.translation: Finally the barbarians removed their helmets,
captions.transcription: kabuto wo nuide hoko wo fuse

captions.translation: lay down their arms and were made to surrender.
captions.transcription: mina kÅsan wo mÅshikeri.

captions.translation: From the time of this Prince's reign, the royal sport of hunting was begun.
captions.transcription: Mikoto no gyÅ yori mikariba wo susume tamaeri.

captions.translation: It was an incident that occurred,
captions.transcription: Koro wa kaminazuki,

captions.translation: on the twentieth day of the Tenth month:
captions.transcription: hatsu ka amari no koto nareba.

captions.translation: Everywhere the autumn tints had faded,
captions.transcription: Yo-mo no momiji mo fuyugare no

captions.translation: and even on the distant winter withered mountains,
captions.transcription: tÅ-yama ni miyuru hatsu-yuki wo,

captions.translation: the traces of the first snow fall could be seen.
captions.transcription: nagame sase tamaishi ni,

captions.translation: [SHITE] The barbarians surrounding him on every side
captions.transcription: [SHITE] Yebisu shihÅ wo kakomitsutsu.

captions.translation: [JIUTAI] Set fire to the grass of the withered fields, and as the blaze burned high
captions.transcription: [JIUTAI] Kare-no no kusa ni hi wo kake

captions.translation: and as the blaze burned high with heavy lingering billows of smoke.
captions.transcription: yo-en shikiri ni moekitari

captions.translation: Began to beat their war drums in the signal to attack.
captions.transcription: kataki semetsuzumi wo uchikakete

captions.translation: The Towering flames! as the attack blazed forward
captions.transcription: ka-en wo hanachite kakarikareba.

captions.translation: [SHITE] The Prince drew his sword
captions.transcription: [SHITE] Mi-koto tsurugi wo nuite...

captions.translation: [JIUTAI] The Prince drawing his sword,
captions.transcription: [JIUTAI] Mi-koto tsurugi wo nuite,

captions.translation: wielded it about him.
captions.transcription: atari wo harai tachimachi.

captions.translation: At once, the flames drew back,
captions.transcription: ni honÅ mo tachishirizoke to,

captions.translation: as it mowed down the grasses in all directions.
captions.transcription: shihÅ no kusa wo nagiharaeba.

captions.translation: The spirit of the sword became a storm
captions.transcription: Tsurugi no seirei arashi to natte,

captions.translation: blasting back the raging flames and grasses too.
captions.transcription: hon wo mo kusa mo fuki-kaesarete.

captions.translation: The blaze lit up the heavens, covered the earth!
captions.transcription: Ten ni kakayaki chi ni michite.

captions.translation: A furnace of fierce flames turned back to devour the enemy forces.
captions.transcription: MyÅka wa kaette kataki wo yakeba.

captions.translation: Thus, the countless barbarians,
captions.transcription: Su man gi no Yebisu-domo wa,

captions.translation: and cavalrymen were brought down.
captions.transcription: tachimachi koko nite usetengeri.

captions.translation: So in later years the Empire was at peace:
captions.transcription: Sono nochi shikai osamarite,

captions.translation: So much so that the people forgot to bar the doors of their houses.
captions.transcription: Jinka tozashi wo wasureshi mo.

captions.translation: This is because of the 'Grass-cutter', it was said.
captions.transcription: Sono Kusanagi no yue to ka ya.

captions.translation: And now, this auspicious omened blade
captions.transcription: Tadaima nanji ga utsubeki

captions.translation: that you must forge!
captions.transcription: kono zuisÅ no mitsurugi mo.

captions.translation: Is there any reason it should be a lesser blade than that ?
captions.transcription: Ika de sore ni wa otorubeki.

captions.translation: Munechika, heir to a house of proud tradition,
captions.transcription: TsutÅru ie no Munechika yo,

captions.translation: set your heart at rest and go home now.
captions.transcription: kokoro yasuku mo omoite ge-kÅ shi tamae.
